        DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN 

             These functions search the string pointed to by _s_t_r_i_n_g for 
             the first instance of the pattern pointed to by _p_a_t_t_e_r_n 
             starting at position _p_o_s (where the first position in a 
             string is 1 not 0). The returned value is the position of 
             the first matched character of the pattern in the string, 
             or zero if a match is not found.  

             FFIINNDDSSTTRR stops searching the string when a null byte is 
             found.  

             FFIINNDDNNSSTTRR only stops searching at position _p_o_s + _l_e_n so it 
             may continue past nulls.  

        CCAAVVEEAATTSS 

             The current implementation does not use the most efficient 
             algorithm for pattern matching so use on very long strings 
             is likely to be somewhat slow.  

